        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>related:</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="1" data-topic="9063">
  <div class="title">
    <div class="quote-controls"></div>
    <img loading="lazy" alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/patrick/40/2848_2.png" class="avatar">
    <a href="https://forums.whonix.org/t/use-xfce-with-wayland/9063">use XFCE with Wayland</a> <a class="badge-wrapper  bullet" href="http://forums.whonix.org/c/development/8"><span class="badge-category-bg" style="background-color: #25AAE2;"></span><span style="" data-drop-close="true" class="badge-category clear-badge" title="Hacking on the Whonix software and code. (devs) (list of components looking for maintainer)">Development</span></a>
  </div>
  <blockquote>
    Most important question: 
could we just swap out the XFCE window manager which isn’t wayland capable and replace it with a wayland capable window manager?
  </blockquote>
</aside>

<aside class="quote quote-modified" data-post="1" data-topic="12324">
  <div class="title">
    <div class="quote-controls"></div>
    <img loading="lazy" alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/tnt_bom_bom/40/2148_2.png" class="avatar">
    <a href="https://forums.whonix.org/t/make-sure-whonix-tools-support-wayland/12324">Make sure whonix tools support wayland</a> <a class="badge-wrapper  bullet" href="http://forums.whonix.org/c/development/8"><span class="badge-category-bg" style="background-color: #25AAE2;"></span><span style="" data-drop-close="true" class="badge-category clear-badge" title="Hacking on the Whonix software and code. (devs) (list of components looking for maintainer)">Development</span></a>
  </div>
  <blockquote>
    Wayland support is becoming almost a must in application development, So its better to make whonix tools ready for that. 
Whonix GUI tools: 

<a href="https://github.com/Whonix/sdwdate-gui" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Sdwdate</a>
<a href="https://github.com/Whonix/systemcheck" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">System Check</a>
<a href="https://github.com/Whonix/setup-wizard-dist" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">First Boot Setup</a>
<a href="https://github.com/Whonix/tor-control-panel" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Tor Control Panel</a>
<a href="https://github.com/Whonix/anon-connection-wizard" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">anon-connection-wizard</a>
Whonix Repository
Tor Browser Downloader (anondist)
Onion Circuits

Not Whonix GUI Apps, But coming by default according to whonix choice: (not sure if any fully support wayland) 

Hexchat
Tor Browser
GPA
KeePassXC
Monero-GUI
Electrum
ZuluCrypt
VLC
xpdf
Xarchiver
Thunderbird
Pul…
  </blockquote>
</aside>

<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="curious_george945" data-post="1" data-topic="15776">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/59ef9b/40.png" class="avatar"> curious_george945:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Is there a timeline for switching to wayland</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>No timeline.<br>
Not a priority. (<a href="https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Reporting_Bugs#Community_Feedback">about priorities</a>)<br>
Probably if/when Xfce supports wayland and that lands in Debian stable.</p>
<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="curious_george945" data-post="1" data-topic="15776">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/59ef9b/40.png" class="avatar"> curious_george945:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>or xpra?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Unlikely since no desktop environment / Linux distribution is using it?</p>
          <p><a href="http://forums.whonix.org/t/x11-sandbox-mitigation/15776/3">Read full topic</a></p>
